			<ns0:name>s...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/108394971971967673680/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Changing the title to more accurately reflect what was intended.  In order to enable vector intrinsics across all architectures we want to be able to assume that stack frames are aligned 0mod16.  Attempting this caused two different sorts of failures:
1) x86-32 with glibc
2) ARM with newlib

(1) was caused by runnable-ld.so not being compiled with the proper option to ensure its stack is aligned 0mod16.
(2)'s cause remains unknown.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-06-01T19:58:50.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-06-01T19:58:50.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates>
			<ns2:status>Accepted</ns2:status><ns2:summary>pnacl stack alignment should be 0mod16</ns2:summary></ns2:updates><ns0:title>Comment 8 by s...@google.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=2665#c8" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/2665/comments/full/8" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>